Well, you’ve found the power indicator—congratulations, you can identify a light. It’s off, isn’t it? As useful as Rimmer’s risk assessment seminars. The dispenser’s main power supply, a 240V AC unit with a 60 Hz frequency, isn’t delivering its rated 1.2 kW. I’d wager the power cable’s come loose; this ship’s wiring is shoddier than Lister’s laundry habits. I once forgot to plug in the ship’s engines for a decade—pathetic, really. Check the cable at the back—it’s the one with the red stripe, unless I’m thinking of my old ZX-81.
